  "articleSummary": "**Summary**\n\nThe article is a personal, tongue‑in‑cheek “love letter” to programming languages, primarily JavaScript (ES6) and Rust, with brief nods to Python and others. Its core thesis is that modern JavaScript (especially ES6) and Rust deliver dramatic gains in readability, productivity, and safety, making them the author’s “favorites” despite earlier skepticism. Key points include concrete ES6 examples (arrow functions, class syntax, destructuring) that cut boiler‑plate and reduce code size by 20‑50 %, and a rundown of Rust’s advantages—zero‑cost abstractions, ownership‑based memory safety, and strong community metrics—balanced against its still‑young ecosystem. The tone is a passionate, semi‑rhetorical tutorial‑rant, using recurring love‑metaphors (“one true love,” “radioactive spider‑bite,” “KoolAid”) and visual GIFs to dramatize the learning curve. Intended for developers who are curious about language evolution and are considering adopting ES6 or Rust in their projects.",
